# =====================================================================
# PRIVACY GUARDRAILS — see privacy/GUARDRAILS.md
# Rule #1: No personal data in git.
#
# Strategy: DENY-BY-DEFAULT for any folder/format that typically holds
# PII (passport scans, bank statements, filled forms, booking
# confirmations, insurance certs).
#
# To track a new file type, you MUST consciously un-ignore it here.
# Audit any change to this file before committing.
# =====================================================================

# ---- PII collection folders ----
# Structure preserved via .gitkeep; contents always ignored.
forms/**
!forms/.gitkeep
appointments/**
!appointments/.gitkeep
insurance/**
!insurance/.gitkeep

# ---- Image formats (passport / BRP / document scans) ----
*.png
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.heic
*.heif
*.webp
*.tiff
*.tif
*.bmp

# ---- Exceptions: Web Store listing assets (versioned screenshots) ----
!extension/screenshots/**/*.png
!extension/screenshots/**/*.jpg
*.gif

# Allow-list: brand/contact assets that ship as part of the extension.
# These are public marketing material (no PII), not document scans.
!extension/public/qrcode/*.png
!extension/public/qrcode/*.jpeg
!extension/public/qrcode/*.jpg
!extension/public/icons/*.png
!extension/public/brand/*.png
!extension/public/brand/*.svg

# ---- Office documents (filled forms, statements, letters) ----
*.docx
*.doc
*.xlsx
*.xls
*.pptx
*.ppt
*.odt
*.ods

# ---- PDFs: deny by default; allow only public reference docs ----
*.pdf
!Term-Dates-*.pdf

# ---- Archives (likely bundles of sensitive docs) ----
*.zip
*.rar
*.7z
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.tgz

# ---- Email / contact exports ----
*.eml
*.msg
*.vcf

# ---- Obsidian: keep small config JSONs, exclude everything else ----
# Plugins are downloaded by Obsidian from the community marketplace when
# the user trusts the vault — never vendor `main.js` / `styles.css` /
# `manifest.json` into git. The committed `community-plugins.json` lists
# which plugins to install, which is the only reproducibility signal
# that matters.
.obsidian/plugins/
.obsidian/snippets/
.obsidian/themes/
.obsidian/workspace.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json
.obsidian/workspace.json.bak
.obsidian/cache

# ---- Build artefacts & dependencies (extension) ----
node_modules/
dist/
.vite/
*.tsbuildinfo

# ---- Tool caches / runtime logs ----
# Playwright MCP captures page snapshots that may contain personal data
# (e.g. France-Visas portal DOM, TLScontact account state). Always ignore.
.playwright-mcp/
*.log

# ---- OS / editor noise ----
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
._*
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/
.cursor/

# ---- Personal application docs (kept LOCAL only) ----
# These contain family-specific context (composition, locations, dates,
# itinerary) that should never reach the public mirror. Generic templates
# with placeholders are tracked under docs/templates/ instead.
/DASHBOARD.md
/visa-workflow.html
/docs/00-family-profile.md
/docs/01-france-visa-requirements.md
/docs/01-italy-visa-requirements.md
/docs/02-document-checklist.md
/docs/03-appointment-booking-guide.md
/docs/04-travel-insurance-guide.md
/docs/05-master-action-plan.md
/docs/06-itinerary-locked.md
/docs/07-bookings-research.md
/privacy/audit-log.md

# ---- Secrets / env (defence in depth — should never exist here anyway) ----
.env
.env.*
*.key
*.pem
*.p12
*.pfx
credentials*
secrets*
